# Development Timelines Principle - QUILT Core Tenet

## Overview
This rule enforces QUILT's Development Timelines Principle: "Don't estimate time. Estimate scope." AI-assisted development is 10-50x faster than historical baselines, making traditional time estimates obsolete.

## Rule: Scope-Based Estimation Required

When discussing or planning work:

### ❌ FORBIDDEN: Time-based language
- "This will take 24 hours"
- "I can finish this in 2 days"  
- "Timeline: 1 week"
- "ETA: Friday"
- "timing"

### ✅ REQUIRED: Scope-based language
- "Scope: Validate Y2K modal styling against spec checklist"
- "Dependencies: Need color hex verification, font family audit, accessibility testing"
- "Deliverables: Spec compliance report with findings and recommendations"
- "Blockers: Need access to implementation files and spec reference"
---
alwaysApply: true
